Package: mfclick
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Modular software router
 Click is a tool for building flexible and configurable routers.
 .
 A click router is assembled from simple elements that implement simple
 functionalities, such as packet classification, queuing, scheduling and
 interfacing with network devices. A click configuration is a graph of
 elements that send each others packets and process them.
 .
 This package provides the userspace tools for using click.
